These are Puzzles for 2x2 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-1::.
There 2 different types of food: asparagus, pear
The people use 2 different means of transport: bus, car
1. the person driving the bus is on the right of the person driving the car##1
2. the person eating asparagus is not to the right of the person driving the car##8

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1    |    2     |
| Food        | asparagus   | pear   |
| Transport   | car | bus |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-2::.
There are 2 different favourite beverages: iced-tea, water
The people prefer 2 different types of sport: handball, badminton
1. the person who's sport is handball is not to the left of the person drinking water##8
2. the person who's sport is handball is somewhere to the right of the person drinking water##5

.:: Answer ::.
|            |    1     |    2    |
| Beverage   | water | iced-tea   |
| Sport      | badminton | handball |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-3::.
There 2 different types of food: cucumber, asparagus
The people prefer 2 different music-genres: ambient, jazz
1. the person eating cucumber is not to the left of the fan of jazz##8
2. the person eating asparagus is on the left of the fan of jazz##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1   |    2    |
| Food          | asparagus | cucumber |
| Music-Genre   | ambient   | jazz     |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x2-Level-8-4::.
